16/12/2009
WASHINGTON, United States -- Serbian Foreign Minister Vuk Jeremic met with Secretary of State Hillary Clinton on Tuesday (December 15th) to discuss bilateral relations and the situation in the Balkans. 
Before the talks, Clinton told journalists that there are positive developments in the US relationship with Serbia. 
Jeremic thanked Washington for supporting Serbia's main strategic priority -- EU membership. 
He added that Clinton has accepted his invitation to visit Belgrade, though no exact timing was mentioned. 
(Beta, Tanjug, RTS - 16/12/09)
